    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1005a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 4, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Department just advised by British Embassy that British Government has
                    instructed British Minister in Lima to make representations to Peruvian
                    Government on basis of Kellogg Pact. British Government gave as reason for its
                    change in attitude that it has now learned that Peruvian troops, as
                    distinguished from Peruvian individuals, are now at Leticia.</p>
                <p>German and Italian Ambassadors state their Ministers have been instructed to act
                    when British and French do so. French Embassy confident its Government will take
                    similar action and that delay is caused by change in French Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
